23 Section 2 sets forth certain bonding requirements for applicants for a restricted
24 license and authorizes a person who has held such a license for not less than 2 years
25 to apply for a contractor’s license that is not a restricted license under certain
26 circumstances. Under section 2, the requirements generally applicable to the
27 issuance and renewal of a contractor’s license do not apply to the issuance and
28 renewal of a restricted license, with certain exceptions. Rather, sections 2 and 3 of
29 this bill require the Board, on or before January 1, 2027, to adopt regulations
30 necessary to provide for the issuance and renewal of a restricted license. The
31 regulations are required to, among other things: (1) establish the monetary limit of a
32 restricted license, which must be $7,000, including labor and materials, or a greater
33 amount that the Board determines to be appropriate; (2) set forth certain application
34 requirements and procedures for the issuance and renewal of a restricted license;
35 and (3) establish reasonable fees associated with the issuance and renewal of a
36 restricted license.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. (Deleted by amendment.)
2 Sec. 2. Chapter 624 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
3 thereto a new section to read as follows:
4 1. The Board may issue a restricted license that authorizes
5 the holder to perform certain work for which a contractor’s
6 license is required, within the scope and monetary limit of the
7 restricted license, to a person who submits to the Board:
8 (a) An application containing any information required by the
9 Board by regulation;
10 (b) Any fees required for the issuance of the license
11 established by the Board by regulation; and
12 (c) Proof satisfactory to the Board that the person:
13 (1) Has not less than 2 years of experience in a trade,
14 which may include, without limitation:
15 (I) Work experience of a particular type or within a
16 particular classification;
17 (II) Alternative training in a program which is offered
18 at an accredited college or university, apprenticeship or equivalent
19 program accepted by the Board; or
20 (III) Completion of any other program or obtaining any
21 other qualification acceptable to the Board; and
22 (2) Completed, within the year immediately preceding the
23 date on which the application is submitted, a course in business
24 counseling or a similar curriculum which consists of a minimum
25 number of hours and any other requirements established by the
26 Board.
27 2. Before issuing a restricted license to an applicant, the
28 Board shall require the applicant to file with the Board a surety
