1 bond or cash deposit in an amount determined by the Board by
2 regulation, which must be not less than $2,000.
3 3. A restricted license issued pursuant to this section is valid
4 for 2 years and may be renewed in accordance with the procedures
5 for the renewal of a restricted license established by the Board by
6 regulation. A person who has held a restricted license for a period
7 of 2 years or more may, in accordance with the provisions of this
8 chapter and the regulations adopted pursuant thereto governing
9 the issuance of a contractor’s license that is not a restricted
10 license, apply for a contractor’s license that is not a restricted
11 license if the person is not the subject of any open or unresolved
12 complaints.
13 4. Except for the provisions of NRS 624.268 and except as
14 otherwise provided by the regulations adopted by the Board
15 pursuant to subsection 7, the provisions of NRS 624.240 to
16 624.288, inclusive, that apply to a contractor’s license that is not a
17 restricted license do not apply to a restricted license issued
18 pursuant to this section.
19 5. A restricted license issued pursuant to this section may
20 only be issued in a classification and subclassification prescribed
21 by the Board which:
22 (a) Authorizes the holder of the restricted license to perform
23 the remodeling and improvement of an existing, detached, stand-
24 alone single-family residence or single-family residential unit
25 within a structure that does not extend more than three stories
26 above the ground and one story below the ground; and
27 (b) Does not authorize the holder of the restricted license to
28 increase the existing enclosed space of the residential structure.
29 6. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the holder of a
30 restricted license issued pursuant to this section may enter into a
31 contract for a construction project that involves one or more
32 building trades or crafts that the Board may determine to be
33 appropriate, which must not include any building trade or craft
34 involving the performance of any work of a type described in
35 paragraph (b) or (c) of subsection 6 of NRS 624.031.
36 7. The Board shall adopt regulations necessary to provide for
37 the issuance and renewal of a restricted license pursuant to this
38 section. The regulations must:
39 (a) Establish the monetary limit for a restricted license, which
40 must be $7,000, including labor and materials, or a greater
41 amount that the Board determines to be appropriate.
42 (b) Set forth the required contents of an application for the
43 issuance or renewal of a restricted license and any additional
44 procedures for the issuance and renewal of a restricted license
45 that the Board determines to be necessary. The regulations must
